      • write

        public boolean write(OutboundFrame frame)
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Queues the OutboundFrame to be written at some point in the future. No guarantee is made that the frame actually is going to be written or received.
        Parameters:
        frame - the frame to write.
        Returns:
        true if the frame was queued; false if rejected.

      • flush

        public void flush()
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Flushes whatever needs to be written. Normally this call doesn't need to be made since Channel.write(OutboundFrame) write the content; but in case of protocol and TLS handshaking, such triggers are needed.

      • lastReadTimeMillis

        public long lastReadTimeMillis()
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Returns the last Clock.currentTimeMillis() a read of the socket was done.
        Returns:
        the last time a read from the socket was done.

      • lastWriteTimeMillis

        public long lastWriteTimeMillis()
        Description copied from interface: Channel
        Returns the last Clock.currentTimeMillis() that a write to the socket completed. Writing to the socket doesn't mean that data has been send or received; it means that data was written to the SocketChannel. It could very well be that this data is stuck somewhere in an io-buffer.
        Returns:
        the last time something was written to the socket.
